cs.RO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper is about service robotics, which is a subfield of robotics that focuses on robots that interact with humans in open-ended, natural environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the need for a mechanism to express variability at design-time that can be efficiently resolved on the robot at run-time based on the then available information, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also introduces a DSL to express run-time variability, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the execution quality of the robot in terms of non-functional properties like safety and task efficiency, which suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
